{{Infobox company | name = China Galaxy Securities | logo = | image = China Galaxy Securities HQ, Beijing.jpg | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = The company headquarters on [[Beijing Financial Street]] | type = public | traded_as = {{ubl|{{SSE|601881}} (A share)|{{hkex|6881}} (H share)|<hr>|[[SSE 50 Index|SSE 50 Component]] (A)}} | foundation = | founder = | location_city = [[Beijing]] | location_country = [[China]] | location = | origins = | key_people = | area_served = | industry = | products = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | owner = | slogan = | homepage = http://www.chinastock.com.cn/ }}
'''China Galaxy Securities Co., Ltd.''' ({{zh|c=中国银河证券股份有限公司}}) is a Chinese brokerage and investment bank.
It raised US$1.1 billion on [[the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong]] in its debut in May 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/05/15/us-chinagalaxy-ipo-idUSBRE94E03S20130515|work=[[Reuters]]|title=China Galaxy IPO raises $1.1 billion, priced for first day pop|author=Elzio Barreto|date=May 15, 2013|accessdate=2015-03-21}}</ref> In January 2015, the company announced plans to issue new shares worth US$2.3 billion on HKSE.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.barrons.com/asiastocks/2015/01/20/china-galaxy-securities-plans-2-3-billion-sale-diluting-shareholders-return/|work=[[Barron's (newspaper)|Barrons]]|title=China Galaxy Securities Plans $2.3 Billion Sale, Diluting Shareholders’ Return|author=Shuli Ren|accessdate=2015-03-21|date=January 20, 2015}}</ref> On 21 April 2015, the company announced in a HKSE filing its plans to raise another US$3.1 billion by selling 2 billion new shares. <ref>{{cite news|title=Galaxy Securities $3.1 Billion Sale to Fuel China Margin Trading|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-04-28/galaxy-securities-3-1-billion-sale-to-fuel-china-margin-trading|accessdate=28 April 2015|publisher=Bloomberg|date=28 April 2015}}</ref>
Since June 2017, it was part of [[Shanghai Stock Exchange]]'s blue chip index: [[SSE 50 Index]].<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.sse.com.cn/market/sseindex/diclosure/c/c_20170531_4318582.shtml|script-title=zh:沪深300、上证50和中证500等指数2017年第一次定期调整样本股|date=31 May 2017|access-date=30 October 2017|publisher=Shanghai Stock Exchange|language=zh-cn}}</ref> ==History== China Galaxy Securities was founded in Jan 26, 2007 with a capital of RMB 6 billion. Major contribution of fund was from Galaxy Financial Holdings which took up 99.89% of issued capital, with the remaining 0.11% being taken up by 4 promotors: Beijing Tsinghua Venture Capital (currently known as Qingyuan Defeng), Chongqing Water, China General and CNBM. <ref>[http://www.chinastock.com.cn/en/aboutus/corporateInformation.jsp Company Corporate Information Retrieved 2018-05-23]</ref>
==Management Board== The board of directors consist of 11 members, of which 2 are executive Directors, 5 non-executive Directors and 4 independent non-executive Directors. Directors are elected on 3-year term. <ref>[http://big5.chinastock.com.cn/en/investorrelations/corporateGovernance_1.jsp Investor relation Retrieved 2018-05-23]</ref>
